, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human HeLa cells", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.8631801605224609, "span": {"begin": 2052, "end": 2068}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9969315528869629, "span": {"begin": 2052, "end": 2057}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:3259"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CCCP", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.982120931148529, "span": {"begin": 2101, "end": 2105}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:30616"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ATP", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9650787115097046, "span": {"begin": 2166, "end": 2169}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:6239"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Caenorhabditis elegans", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9792798757553101, "span": {"begin": 2234, "end": 2256}}, {"id": ["mesh:C015001"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Arsenite", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984819293022156, "span": {"begin": 2272, "end": 2280}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:30616"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ATP", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.995361864566803, "span": {"begin": 2355, "end": 2358}}], "text": "The empirical support of Relationship 2203 is considered high.  Rationale: The majority of relevant studies show good incidence, temporal and/or dose concordance in different organisms and cell types after exposure to known uncouplers, with relatively few exceptions.  Evidence:    Temporal concordance: Exposure of zebrafish embryos to 0.5 &micro;M of the classical uncoupler 2,4-DNP led to significantly uncoupling of OXPHOS after 21h, whereas significant reduction in ATP was only observed after 45h&nbsp;(Bestman 2015).   Dose concordance: The uncoupler triclosan induced significant uncoupling of OXPHOS in zebrafish embryos at 15 &micro;M, whereas higher (30 &micro;M) concentration was required to caused significant ATP depletion&nbsp;&nbsp;(Shim 2016).  Dose concordance: Exposure to 1 &micro;M of of the uncoupler CCCP led to 40% uncoupling of OXPHOS in rat RBL-2H3 cells, whereas the same magnitude of effect for ATP reduction required 1.6 &micro;M of CCCP (Weatherly 2016).  Dose concordance: Exposure to 10 &micro;M of the uncoupler triclosan caused significant uncoupling of OXPHOS in rat RBL-2H3 cells, whereas significant reduction in ATP was observed at a higher concentration (30 &micro;M)&nbsp;&nbsp;(Weatherly 2018).  Dose concordance: Significant effect on uncoupling of OXPHOS required &nbsp;2 &micro;M FCCP, whereas a significant reduction in ATP required 20 &micro;M FCCP in human RD cells&nbsp;&nbsp;(Kuruvilla 2003).  Incidence concordance: In human colon cancer cells (SW480), exposure to 150 &micro;M of the uncoupler flavanoid morin caused 60% reduction in MMP, whereas only around 35% decrease in ATP&nbsp;&nbsp;(Sithara 2017).  Incidence concordance: Exposure of rat RBL-2H3 cells to 10 &micro;M &nbsp;of the uncoupler triclosan led to 50% uncoupling of OXPHOS, whereas only 40% reduction in ATP (Weatherly 2016).  Incidence concordance: Exposure to 5 &micro;M of the uncoupler CCCP caused 71% uncoupling of OXPHOS, whereas only 64% reduction of ATP in human HL-60 cells (Sweet 1999).  Incidence concordance: Exposure of human HeLa cells to 50 &micro;M of the uncoupler CCCP for 1h led to 77% uncoupling of OXPHOS and 25% reduction in ATP (Koczor 2009).  Incidence concordance: Exposure of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans to 50 &micro;M Arsenite for 1h led to approximately 45% uncoupling of OXPHOS and 20% reduction in ATP (Luz 2016).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:06:17 +0000 2026"}